Project IceStorm – iCE40 HX1K LOGIC Tile (1 15)

Project IceStorm aims at documenting the bitstream format of Lattice iCE40 FPGAs and providing simple tools for analyzing and creating bitstream files. This is work in progress.

This page describes the LOGIC Tile (1 15), what nets and configuration bits it has and how it is connected to its neighbourhood.

Configuration Bitmap

A LOGIC Tile has 864 config bits in 16 groups of 54 bits each:
 B0[53:0],  B1[53:0],  B2[53:0],  B3[53:0],  B4[53:0],  B5[53:0],  B6[53:0],  B7[53:0],
 B8[53:0],  B9[53:0], B10[53:0], B11[53:0], B12[53:0], B13[53:0], B14[53:0], B15[53:0]
